        <Parent_String>Chokwe-Lunda [300016281], Southwestern Democratic Republic of Congo and Angola styles [300016228], Central African (cultural or regional style) [300016168], African by cultural or regional designation [300121001], African (general, continental cultures) [300015647], styles, periods, and cultures by region [300111079], Styles and Periods (hierarchy name) [300015646], Styles and Periods Facet [300264088]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to the culture of the Bantu-speaking people inhabiting the southern Congo and northeastern Angola. They comprise many aboriginal peoples and conquering groups of Lunda origin, and they speak a language of the Benue-Congo branch of the Niger-Congo languages. They are hunters or agriculturalists, depending upon which region they inhabit. They live primarily in woodland savanna and strips of rainforest along rivers. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000046363/Encyclopedia Britannica Online (1994-2001)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Se refiere al pueblo de cultura bantu-parlante que habita el sur del Congo y noreste de Angola. Comprenden una serie de pueblos aborígenes y grupos conquistadores de origen lunda y que hablan una rama de la lengua benue-congo, una lengua del Níger-Congo. Son cazadores y agricultores, dependiendo de la región que habiten. Ellos viven primordialmente en la sabana boscosa y en zonas angostas a lo largo de ríos de selva lluviosa.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Verwijst naar de cultuur van het Bantu-sprekende volk dat in de zuidelijke Congo en noordoostelijk Angola woonde. Tot dit volk behoren veel inheemse volken en groepen veroveraars van Lunda-origine, en deze spreken een taal van de Benue-Congo-tak van de Niger-Congo-talen. Het zijn jagers en landbouwers, afhankelijk van welke regio ze bewonen. Ze wonen voornamelijk in bossavannes en stroken regenwoud langs rivieren.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052378/Winkler Prins Encyclopedie (1990)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>指稱居住於剛果南部及安哥拉東北部說班圖語族的文化。喬奎人包括許多原住民族以及來自隆達的征服者民族，所用語言屬於尼日－剛果語系中的貝努埃－剛果語支，依所住區域不同，可能以捕獵或務農為生，主要居住在熱帶稀樹草原林地以及河流沿岸的雨林地帶。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
